GATEWAY, IBM, AND OTHER ANTITRUST AND COMPETITION LAW MATTERS. HEADCOUNT-RELATED COSTS INCREASED 5% DURING THE TWELVE MONTHS ENDED JUNE 30, 2006 REFLECTING BOTH A 23% INCREASE IN HEADCOUNT AND AN INCREASE IN SALARIES AND BENEFITS FOR EXISTING

