DECREASED COSTS FOR LEGAL SETTLEMENTS AND LEGAL CONTINGENCIES. WE INCURRED $1.32 BILLION IN LEGAL CHARGES DURING FISCAL YEAR 2006 AS COMPARED TO $2.31 BILLION IN LEGAL CHARGES INCURRED DURING FISCAL YEAR 2005. HEADCOUNT-RELATED COSTS INCREASED 7%

