, FILED IN THE U.S. DISTRICT COURT FOR THE WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON ON MAY 18, 2006, A SUBSIDIARY OF SYMANTEC HAS FILED AN ACTION ASSERTING

CLAIMS OF TRADE SECRET MISAPPROPRIATION, BREACH OF CONTRACT, AND PATENT INFRINGEMENT RELATING TO CERTAIN STORAGE TECHNOLOGIES. ADVERSE OUTCOMES IN SOME OR ALL OF THE MATTERS DESCRIBED IN THIS PARAGRAPH MAY RESULT IN SIGNIFICANT MONETARY DAMAGES OR

INJUNCTIVE RELIEF AGAINST US, ADVERSELY AFFECTING DISTRIBUTION OF OUR OPERATING SYSTEM OR APPLICATION PRODUCTS. THE RISKS ASSOCIATED WITH AN ADVERSE DECISION MAY RESULT IN MATERIAL SETTLEMENTS.

OTHER.

