OUTCOMES WHICH WE ESTIMATE COULD BE UP TO $1.0 BILLION IN AGGREGATE BEYOND RECORDED AMOUNTS. WERE AN UNFAVORABLE FINAL OUTCOME TO OCCUR, THERE EXISTS THE POSSIBILITY OF A MATERIAL ADVERSE IMPACT ON THE COMPANYS FINANCIAL POSITION AND ON THE

RESULTS OF OPERATIONS FOR THE PERIOD IN WHICH THE EFFECT BECOMES REASONABLY ESTIMABLE.

